Steps...
(1)First Download the Mortality Files from the CDC.
https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/data_access/vitalstatsonline.htm#Mortality_Multiple
(2)Run the CDC Mortality Parser on the downloaded CDC File
(3)Import the CDC file into Juypter
(4)Analyze the data in the file.  
(Extra) There are several Kaggle Kernals showing various data analysis. 
(Extra2) The .py file will run the .ipynb file and produce the graphs in a local folder of your choice
